<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_029760"><name>1VD-FTV ENGINE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0135360"><name>ECD SYSTEM</name><para id="RM100000000FJJN" category="C"><dtccode>P0405</dtccode><dtcname>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor &quot;A&quot; Circuit Low</dtcname><dtccode>P0406</dtccode><dtcname>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor &quot;A&quot; Circuit High</dtcname><dtccode>P0407</dtccode><dtcname>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor &quot;B&quot; Circuit Low</dtcname><dtccode>P0408</dtccode><dtcname>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor &quot;B&quot; Circuit High</dtcname><subpara id="RM100000000FJJN_01" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The EGR valve position sensor is mounted on the EGR valve and used for detecting the lift amount of the valve. The lift amount detected by the sensor is provided to the ECM as feedback. The ECM then regulates the lift amount of the valve in accordance with engine running conditions.</ptxt><table type="dtc-explan-table" pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="6"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.42in"/><colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.70in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Detection Item</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>MIL</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Memory</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0405</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor &quot;A&quot; Circuit Low</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>No. 1 EGR valve position sensor output voltage is less than 0.1 V for more than 5 seconds</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in No. 1 EGR valve position sensor circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No. 1 EGR valve (EGR valve position sensor)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0406</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor &quot;A&quot; Circuit High</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>No. 1 EGR valve position sensor output voltage is more than 4.9 V for more than 5 seconds</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in No. 1 EGR valve position sensor circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No. 1 EGR valve (EGR valve position sensor)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0407</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor &quot;B&quot; Circuit Low</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>No. 2 EGR valve position sensor output voltage is less than 0.1 V for more than 5 seconds</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in No. 2 EGR valve position sensor circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No. 2 EGR valve (EGR valve position sensor)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0408</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor &quot;B&quot; Circuit High</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>No. 2 EGR valve position sensor output voltage is more than 4.9 V for more than 5 seconds</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in No. 2 EGR valve position sensor circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No. 2 EGR valve (EGR valve position sensor)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJJN_02" category="03"><name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>When the output voltage of the EGR valve position sensor deviates from the normal operating range of 0.1 to 4.9 V for more than 0.5 seconds, the ECM interprets this as a malfunction of the sensor circuit, and illuminates the MIL.</ptxt></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJJN_03" category="03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><ptxt>Refer to DTC P0400.</ptxt><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJK0_03"/></mlink></ptxt></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJJN_04" category="10"><name>CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT</name><content5><atten3><ptxt>After replacing the ECM, the new ECM needs registration (See page <mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJKB"/></mlink>) and initialization (See page <mlink><xref label="Seep00002" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FJIX"/></mlink>).</ptxt></atten3><atten4><ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the GTS. Freeze frame data records the engine condition when malfunctions are detected. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can help determine if the vehicle was moving or stationary, if the engine was warmed up or not, and other data from the time the malfunction occurred.</ptxt></atten4></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM100000000FJJN_06" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM100000000FJJN_06_0007" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (EGR VALVE POWER SOURCE)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the C47 or C66 EGR valve connector.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="A165766C04" width="3.434793307in" height="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>No. 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>No. 2</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to EGR Valve)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the voltage according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard voltage</title><table><title>No. 1</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Switch Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C47-3 (VC) - C47-2 (E2)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Ignition switch ON</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>4.5 to 5.5 V</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table><title>No. 2</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Switch Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>C66-3 (VC) - C66-2 (E2)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Ignition switch ON</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>4.5 to 5.5 V</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="1-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-1" childid="RM100000000FJJN_06_0001"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="1-4"><action actiontype="jump" cellposition="2-4" childid="RM100000000FJJN_06_0006"><actiontitle>GO TO STEP 3</actiontitle></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000FJJN_06_0001" cellposition="2-1"><testtitle>INSPECT EGR VALVE ASSEMBLY (NO. 1 OR NO. 2) (POSITION SENSOR)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the C47 or C66 EGR valve connector.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="A165764C02" width="3.434793307in" height="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Component without harness connected</ptxt><ptxt>(EGR Valve)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard resistance</title><table><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>3 (VC) - 2 (E2)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>20°C (68°F)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>2.45 to 4.55 kΩ</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>4 (EGLS) - 2 (E2)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>20°C (68°F)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>2.45 to 4.55 kΩ</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="2-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="3-1" childid="RM100000000FJJN_06_0006"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="2-3"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-3"><actiontitle>REPLACE EGR VALVE ASSEMBLY (NO. 1 OR NO. 2)</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FDIB"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM100000000FJJN_06_0006" cellposition="3-1"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (EGR VALVE - ECM)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the C47 or C66 EGR valve connector.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="A311467C04" width="3.434793307in" height="4.677165354in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>No. 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>No. 2</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of 